Package SimulationData

Interface SimulationDataInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
SimulationData
public interface SimulationDataInterface
SimulationDataInterface.java This interface defines the methods for the SimulationData class, providing methods to parse command line arguments, generate cost matrices, and access various simulation parameters. Created on 01/06/2024
Since:
1.0

  • Method Details

    • comand_line_arguments_parser

      void comand_line_arguments_parser(String[] args)
      Parses command line arguments. This method is responsible for parsing the command line arguments provided to the simulation. It extracts and processes the necessary parameters required to configure and run the simulation.
      Parameters:
      args - The command line arguments.

    • file_parser

      void file_parser()
      Parses the input file. This method handles the parsing of an input file to extract simulation parameters and data. It should read the file and populate the relevant fields and structures required for the simulation.

    • cost_matrix_generation

      void cost_matrix_generation()
      Generates the cost matrix. This method is responsible for generating the cost matrix used in the simulation. The cost matrix typically represents costs or distances between different entities or locations in the simulation.
